INSERT Articles ( Title, UrlSlug, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId, SiteId, Language ) VALUES ( N'ANALOG Computing', N'analog-computing', N'ANALOG Computing was an American computer magazine that focused on the Atari 8-bit family of home computers. It was published from 1981 to 1989 and became one of the most popular and influential publications for Atari enthusiasts during that time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The magazine covered a wide range of topics related to Atari computers, including hardware reviews, software recommendations, programming tutorials, game reviews, and tips and tricks for getting the most out of the Atari 8-bit machines. It catered to both beginner and advanced users, providing a wealth of information and resources to help readers make the most of their Atari computers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'ANALOG Computing featured regular columns written by experts in the Atari community, as well as articles contributed by readers. It was known for its in-depth technical articles that delved into programming techniques and advanced hardware modifications. The magazine also included game listings and source code that readers could type in manually to create their own programs or modify existing ones.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'One of the standout features of ANALOG Computing was its extensive coverage of games. The magazine reviewed new Atari games, offered strategies and hints to help players overcome challenges, and often included exclusive game content like maps, level editors, or cheat codes. It also organized game programming contests where readers could submit their own games for a chance to win prizes.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'In addition to its print publication, ANALOG Computing released software on floppy disks, including games and utilities, which readers could purchase separately. The magazine fostered a sense of community among Atari users, providing a platform for them to share their creations, exchange ideas, and connect with fellow enthusiasts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Unfortunately, despite its popularity, ANALOG Computing ceased publication in 1989 due to the declining market for Atari 8-bit computers and the overall changing landscape of the home computer industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Nevertheless, ANALOG Computing remains a significant part of the Atari community''s history, and many Atari enthusiasts look back fondly on the magazine as a valuable resource that contributed to their enjoyment and understanding of the Atari 8-bit computers.', 'Article created', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40', 1, 'en' );
INSERT Articles ( Title, UrlSlug, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId, SiteId, Language ) VALUES ( N'7ball', N'7ball', N'7ball was a Christian music magazine that was first published in 1995. It was known for its in-depth coverage of Christian music, including album reviews, interviews with artists, and features on the latest trends in the genre. The magazine was published by Cornerstone Publishing, which also produced other Christian publications like Cornerstone Magazine and Risen Magazine.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The magazine''s title, "7ball," was a reference to the Magic 8-Ball toy, with the number 7 being significant in Christian symbolism. The magazine''s tagline was "the music magazine with an attitude," reflecting its commitment to covering Christian music in a way that was both informative and edgy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Over the years, 7ball became one of the most popular Christian music magazines, winning several awards for its journalism and design. It was known for its bold and colorful layout, featuring striking graphics and eye-catching typography.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The magazine covered a wide range of genres within Christian music, including rock, hip-hop, pop, and worship. It featured interviews with both established and up-and-coming artists, as well as reviews of new and classic albums. 7ball also featured regular columns on topics like music industry news, cultural trends, and faith and spirituality.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'In addition to its print publication, 7ball also had an online presence, with a website that offered additional content and resources for readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'However, despite its popularity, 7ball was eventually discontinued, with its final issue published in 2006. The decline of the print magazine industry and changes in the Christian music scene were cited as reasons for its discontinuation. Nevertheless, 7ball remains a significant part of Christian music history, remembered by many fans and industry professionals as a valuable resource that helped shape and define the genre.', 'Article created', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40', 1, 'en' );
INSERT Articles ( Title, UrlSlug, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId, SiteId, Language ) VALUES ( N'7x7', N'7x7', N'7x7 was a prominent lifestyle magazine that focused on city living in the San Francisco Bay Area, USA. It covered a wide range of topics including fashion, lifestyle, food, culture, opinion, and entertainment. The magazine aimed to provide readers with an insider''s perspective on the vibrant and diverse aspects of San Francisco and the surrounding region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The name "7x7" referred to the seven-by-seven square miles of the city of San Francisco, highlighting the publication''s focus on the city''s unique attributes and local experiences. The magazine celebrated the Bay Area''s distinct character, featuring articles and features that showcased the latest trends, events, and notable personalities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '7x7 magazine covered fashion and style, highlighting local designers, boutiques, and fashion trends in the Bay Area. It provided readers with fashion editorials, shopping guides, and style advice to keep them informed about the latest fashion happenings in the region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The magazine also delved into lifestyle topics, exploring the city''s diverse neighborhoods, home design, travel recommendations, and profiles of local personalities. It aimed to capture the essence of living in the Bay Area, offering insights into the urban lifestyle and experiences unique to the region.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Food and dining were major focal points for 7x7. The magazine featured restaurant reviews, chef interviews, and culinary event coverage, showcasing the vibrant food scene in the Bay Area. It also shared recipes, wine recommendations, and guides to help readers navigate the local dining landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Additionally, 7x7 covered cultural events, music, art exhibitions, theater performances, and film festivals, keeping readers informed about the latest happenings in the Bay Area''s arts and entertainment scene.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Opinion pieces and articles discussing local issues and trends were also included in the magazine, offering readers a platform to engage in discussions about topics affecting the community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'While the print version of 7x7 magazine has ceased publication, the brand has continued to maintain a digital presence through its website and social media channels. This allows them to continue sharing content and engaging with readers, even though the print magazine is no longer in circulation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Throughout its tenure, 7x7 served as a valuable resource for both residents and visitors, providing an insider''s guide to the dynamic and ever-evolving city of San Francisco and the surrounding Bay Area.', 'Article created', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40', 1, 'en' );
INSERT Articles ( Title, UrlSlug, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId, SiteId, Language ) VALUES ( N'032c', N'032c', N'032c is a highly regarded bi-annual contemporary culture magazine that encompasses a diverse range of topics, including art, fashion, politics, and beyond. It was established in 2001 by Joerg Koch, a German editor and creative director, and is based in Berlin, Germany.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'The magazine takes its name from the Pantone code for red (032) and the standard Cyan color (c), symbolizing its focus on visual aesthetics and design. 032c is known for its visually striking layouts, high-quality photography, and thought-provoking content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'One of the key aspects of 032c is its multidisciplinary approach, covering a broad spectrum of subjects and blending fashion, art, and politics seamlessly. The magazine features in-depth interviews, articles, essays, and visual portfolios that explore the intersections between contemporary culture and society.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'In the realm of fashion, 032c provides coverage of cutting-edge designers, emerging trends, and fashion shows, while also delving into the cultural and societal influences that shape the industry. The magazine often challenges established norms and investigates the political and economic aspects of fashion.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + 'Within the art world, 032c showcases the work of established and emerging artists, highlighting their creative processes, exhibitions, and contributions to contemporary art. It explores diverse art forms and practices, ranging from painting and sculpture to photography, performance, and new media.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + '032c also devotes attention to political and social issues, offering critical perspectives on current affairs, global events, and cultural phenomena. The maga